        <briefdescription>
<para>Calculates how many GameObjects should be spawned this frame. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Called each frame by the spawn system to determine how many objects to activate from the pool. The implementation may consider elapsed time, pool capacity, game state, or any other relevant factors.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>gameWorld</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the current <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1game_1_1GameWorld" kindref="compound">GameWorld</ref>. May be nullptr. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>level</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the current <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1game_1_1Level" kindref="compound">Level</ref> containing bounds and spawn info. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>gameObjectPool</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
