    <briefdescription>
<para>Abstract base class defining when and how many GameObjects should spawn. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1game_1_1SpawnCondition" kindref="compound">SpawnCondition</ref> implements the Strategy pattern for spawn timing control. Concrete implementations determine how many objects should be spawned each frame based on time, game state, pool availability, or other conditions.</para>
<para>The spawn budget returned by `spawnBudget()` represents the number of GameObjects that the spawn system should attempt to activate this frame.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1game_1_1TimerSpawnCondition" kindref="compound">TimerSpawnCondition</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>GameObjectSpawnSystem </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
